{
  "book_id": "ISA",
  "book_name": "Isaiah",
  "chapter": 21,
  "verses": 17,
  "content": [
    {
      "text": "Fallen, Fallen Is Babylon",
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "text": "The oracle concerning the wilderness of the sea.",
      "verse": 1,
      "type": "newline"
    },
    {
      "text": "As whirlwinds in the Negeb sweep on,",
      "verse": 1,
      "type": "poetry newline"
    },
    {
      "text": "it comes from the wilderness,",
      "verse": 1,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "from a terrible land.",
      "verse": 1,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "A stern vision is told to me;",
      "verse": 2,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "the traitor betrays,",
      "verse": 2,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "and the destroyer destroys.",
      "verse": 2,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "Go up, O Elam;",
      "verse": 2,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "lay siege, O Media;",
      "verse": 2,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "all the sighing she has caused",
      "verse": 2,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "I bring to an end.",
      "verse": 2,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "Therefore my loins are filled with anguish;",
      "verse": 3,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "pangs have seized me,",
      "verse": 3,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "like the pangs of a woman in labor;",
      "verse": 3,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "I am bowed down so that I cannot hear;",
      "verse": 3,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "I am dismayed so that I cannot see.",
      "verse": 3,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "My heart staggers; horror has appalled me;",
      "verse": 4,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "the twilight I longed for",
      "verse": 4,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "has been turned for me into trembling.",
      "verse": 4,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "They prepare the table,",
      "verse": 5,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "they spread the rugs,",
      "verse": 5,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "they eat, they drink.",
      "verse": 5,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "Arise, O princes;",
      "verse": 5,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "oil the shield!",
      "verse": 5,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "For thus the Lord said to me:",
      "verse": 6,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "“Go, set a watchman;",
      "verse": 6,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "let him announce what he sees.",
      "verse": 6,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "When he sees riders, horsemen in pairs,",
      "verse": 7,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "riders on donkeys, riders on camels,",
      "verse": 7,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "let him listen diligently,",
      "verse": 7,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "very diligently.”",
      "verse": 7,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "Then he who saw cried out:",
      "verse": 8,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "“Upon a watchtower I stand, O Lord,",
      "verse": 8,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "continually by day,",
      "verse": 8,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "and at my post I am stationed",
      "verse": 8,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "whole nights.",
      "verse": 8,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "And behold, here come riders,",
      "verse": 9,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "horsemen in pairs!”",
      "verse": 9,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "And he answered,",
      "verse": 9,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "“Fallen, fallen is Babylon;",
      "verse": 9,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "and all the carved images of her gods",
      "verse": 9,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "he has shattered to the ground.”",
      "verse": 9,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "O my threshed and winnowed one,",
      "verse": 10,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "what I have heard from the Lord of hosts,",
      "verse": 10,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "the God of Israel, I announce to you.",
      "verse": 10,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "The oracle concerning Dumah.",
      "verse": 11,
      "type": "newline"
    },
    {
      "text": "One is calling to me from Seir,",
      "verse": 11,
      "type": "poetry newline"
    },
    {
      "text": "“Watchman, what time of the night?",
      "verse": 11,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "Watchman, what time of the night?”",
      "verse": 11,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "The watchman says:",
      "verse": 12,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "“Morning comes, and also the night.",
      "verse": 12,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "If you will inquire, inquire;",
      "verse": 12,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "come back again.”",
      "verse": 12,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "The oracle concerning Arabia.",
      "verse": 13,
      "type": "newline"
    },
    {
      "text": "In the thickets in Arabia you will lodge,",
      "verse": 13,
      "type": "poetry newline"
    },
    {
      "text": "O caravans of Dedanites.",
      "verse": 13,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "To the thirsty bring water;",
      "verse": 14,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "meet the fugitive with bread,",
      "verse": 14,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "O inhabitants of the land of Tema.",
      "verse": 14,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "For they have fled from the swords,",
      "verse": 15,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "from the drawn sword,",
      "verse": 15,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "from the bent bow,",
      "verse": 15,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "and from the press of battle.",
      "verse": 15,
      "type": "poetry"
    },
    {
      "text": "For thus the Lord said to me, “Within a year, according to the years of a hired worker, all the glory of Kedar will come to an end.",
      "verse": 16,
      "type": "newline"
    },
    {
      "text": "And the remainder of the archers of the mighty men of the sons of Kedar will be few, for the Lord, the God of Israel, has spoken.”",
      "verse": 17
    }
  ]
}